# 3.1.1.research.external.q10.token-refresh-mechanism

## question

how does Claude Code refresh auth tokens for an ALREADY ACTIVE session? does it re-read env vars, or only use apiKeyHelper?

## options

- env vars read once at spawn (cached) — rotation via env var won't work mid-session
- env vars re-read periodically — rotation via env var will work mid-session
- apiKeyHelper called periodically — rotation via helper works mid-session
- combination

## why it matters

if Claude Code caches env var at spawn, we CANNOT swap auth mid-session by env var changes. we MUST use apiKeyHelper.

## research approach

check Claude Code auth docs, test empirically, verify token refresh behavior for active sessions.

## .status

awaited
